==Western Apache==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|[ʤàː]}}

===Etymology===

From Proto-Athabascan *''-ǯəγe·ʔ''. 

Cognates: Navajo ''-jaa’'', Chiricahua ''-jaa'', Jicarilla ''-jaa'', Plains Apache ''-jaghe''.

===Noun===
'''-jaa''' (''[[inalienable]]'', e.g., '''shijaa''' "my ear", '''bijaa''' "her/his/their ear")

# [[ear]], outer ear

The form '''-jaa''' occurs in the San Carlos varieties; '''-jaa’''' occurs in White Mountain and Dilze’eh (Tonto).

